    "actions_taken": [
      "Injured person evaluated and treated by rig medic",
      "Injured person transported by crew change helicopter to UTMB in Galveston Texas for further evaluation and treatment"
    ],
    "summary": "On December 3, 2015 at 0420 hours, two FMC employees were descending a second set of stairs from the rig floor to the FMCTI connex box. The injured person (IP) lost footing while following a co-worker and fell forward, striking her face on a tread. She sustained severe injuries to her mouth and teeth. The IP was not utilizing the required trailing hand technique and her left thumb struck the vertical rail of the handrail, causing her hand to break free.",
